=========FROM
Docker start form from instruction

   docker build -t from:v1 .
 docker images
 docker tag from:v1  dharma006/from:v1
 docker images
 docker login
 docker login -u dharma006
docker push dharma006/from:v1 it will push oimahge to our docker hub 

docker run -d image-name --> this will create a container

========RUN INstruction=====
RUN is used to install some packages , run some commands

one image can have multiple run instructions

=====CMD=========
after intalling we need to run as container, i.e image to container
cmd is used while creating container form image

RUN VS CMD

RUN = this is used while creating image, we can run multiple run commands but not cmd commands
CMD = this is run while creating a container
if we give multiple cmd then last cmd instruction woill be override

=====LABLEl=====
labe;ls are simple metadata, like tags

labels are mainly used for adding tags to images used fwhile filter

docker images --filter="label=author=dharma" --> this command is used to fetch your image with name dharma form out of 100 images

====EXPOSE====

expose is used to give information abpout the port that is been used for image, it won't open port

